                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/10–2744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-01T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 1, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>653. Urtels 787, Oct. 27 and 795, October 30. You are authorized to give the
                    Soviet and British Ambassadors a copy of your note to the <pb facs="0478"
                        n="466" xml:id="pg_466"/> Prime Minister. While concurrence of the Iranian
                    Government is not strictly necessary, you will doubtless wish to clear with
                    Saed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
